name: Defeat 03 - John F Kenndedy
description:
The assassination of John F. Kennedy (1917-1963), thirty-fifth president of the United States, took place on Friday, November 22, 1963, in Dallas, Texas, United States at 12:30 p.m. m. Kennedy was fatally shot while driving in the presidential car in Dealey Square.1 2 He was the fourth US president to be assassinated (with Abraham Lincoln, James Abram Garfield, and William McKinley) and the eighth to die in office. of its functions.

Three official investigations concluded that Lee Harvey Oswald, an employee of the Texas School Book Depository in Dealey Plaza, was the killer. One of them concluded that Oswald acted alone and another suggested that he acted with at least one other person. The murder is still subject to speculation, it is the origin of a large number of conspiracy theories.

DEFEAT is a collection based on people whose death historically had an impact on power, quite remarkable in history, either by homicide, convictions or natural deaths, these people marked the beginning, or the end of a corrupt era within universal history.
